# Models — figures/CSVs/metrics are tracked, and so are the XGBoost weights
# (~3MB each) since the deployed app loads them directly at runtime
# (recommend.py has no code path that retrains on the fly). Prophet's
# serialized models are NOT loaded by the app (only used for the one-off
# Phase 3 backtest comparison, whose results are already saved as metrics
# JSON/figures), so those stay ignored.
models/prophet_*.json

